  "id": "",
  "summary": "nolimit-x ships large set of heavily obfuscated scripts under.ad/",
  "details": "The package ships 45+ JavaScript files under a hidden.ad/ directory (from-generator.js, phone-validator.js, sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, web-command.js, x0.js through xz.js) that are all heavily obfuscated with hex-mangled identifiers (e.g. _0x4b21d9, _0x2ae857,...). File names such as sms-providers.js, smtp-health-cache.js, phone-validator.js, and web-command.js suggest SMS/SMTP delivery and remote-command functionality, and the obfuscation prevents direct verification of what those scripts do. Without de-obfuscated tracing of the import/lifecycle paths it cannot be confirmed whether installer-side harm (network exfiltration, credential access, remote command execution) occurs at install or import time, but the high opacity, the unusual hidden.ad/ layout, and the suggestive file names warrant human review before this version is allowed.",
